  "chunk_index": 29,
  "summary": "Tom Hargreaves meets with Detective Inspector Crome to report findings regarding the suspect, Alexander Bonaparte Cast (referred to as A.B. Case or Cash). Tom and his girlfriend, Lily, investigated whether Cast's initials match the killer's and tracked his whereabouts during the first murder in Andover. They discovered that on June 21st, the day Bert Smith's boat docked at Southampton, Cast was not at home because Mrs. Marbury had provided a bed for her visiting brother from Canada instead of Smith.\n\nTom also reports that Mrs. Marbury observed Cast acting strangely, specifically by buying numerous newspapers and talking to himself. Inspector Crome notes that this behavior aligns with a witness named Hill, who saw a man talking to himself after watching a movie at the Athena Theatre in Toke. Crome decides to have people monitor a location in Camden Town, consult with the Assistant Police Commissioner, and bring a flustered Mr. Cast to the station for a statement.\n\nAfter the meeting, Tom informs Lily of the investigation. Later, at Mrs. Marbury's house, Cast receives a telephone call. To deflect suspicion regarding his odd behavior, Cast lies to Mrs. Marbury, claiming his sister has just had a son. This lie eases her suspicions. As Cast prepares to leave, he reflects on the telephone call, which had warned him that a detective inspector from Scotland Yard might visit him.",
